Steps : 

1. Create spring boot starter project, add dependancy---spring data jpa, mysql connector
2. in project properties, add db config data as : username, password, dialect, name,url, ddl auto.
3. create entity class
4. create interface repository extending either JpaRespository(child interface of CrudRepository) or CrudRepository.
5. in main method, create ApplicationContext object, after that getBean of step 4 repository(interface repository dont need to create class).
6. create entity object, set values in it.
7. then to save in db, use step 5 reference.save(entity).
8. Done
